						               													<description>Grab your die!&amp;#10;Roll as fast as you can!&amp;#10;Slap your opponent's hands to kill!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Bitch Slap is a revolutionary real-time fighting game that features actual physical contact. Think of the children's game 'Red Hands' taken to a new level with characters, equipment, dirty tricks, dice rolling and awesome art.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a world where female is the dominant sex, Manga-style gladiators enter the arena for deadly battle to appease the crowd, or clowns fight in ridiculous ways for the crowd's favor and laughter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the first phase of the game, each player acquires three characters and equips them with items and techniques either through quick play (that last one minute) or auction (that lasts five minutes).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the second phase of the game, one character from each side enters the arena and special abilities are resolved. On the count of three, each player starts rolling their die as fast as they can (d8 for gladiators, d10 for clowns). On a roll of 1, your character succeeded to Hit. You then have to swing your hand in order to contact your opponent's hand, if successful you Wound, if unsuccessful you Miss. Most characters die when wounded twice, then another character enters the battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When you kill all three of your opponent's gladiators/clowns you are victorious!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Bitch Slap is an official entry to the 3rd annual Greek board game design contest scheduled for Spring 2012&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
